'''''N,N&prime;''-Diisopropylcarbodiimide''' is a [[carbodiimide]] used in [[peptide synthesis]]. As a liquid, it is easier to handle than the commonly used [[Dicyclohexylcarbodiimide|''N,N&prime;''-dicyclohexylcarbodiimide]], a waxy solid. In addition, [[Urea#Related_compounds | N,N'-diisopropylurea]], the byproduct of its use in many chemical reactions, is soluble in most [[organic solvents]], a property that facilitates [[Work-up (chemistry)|work-up]].

